cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.DS 

This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it deals with efficient search and retrieval of similar items in recommendation systems and word embeddings. It also involves clustering algorithms, which are commonly used in IR. 

The paper may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it proposes a new approach for solving the MIPS problem using a variant of the k-means clustering algorithm. 

Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) are also possible sub-categories as the proposed method can be applied to word embeddings and recommendation systems, which are relevant to these fields. 

Finally, the paper may belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category as it compares different approaches for solving the MIPS problem and proposes a new method based on clustering.
